<p>Dear Parents,</p>
<p>This email confirms [FIRST_NAME]'s appointment with Dr Geshani Jayasuriya on [APPOINTMENT_DATE] at [APPOINTMENT_TIME] at the Woolcock Clinic.</p>
<p><strong>Registration</strong></p>
<p>Please <a href="https://wimr.snapforms.com.au/form/registration?new%20patient=[PATIENT]&adult%20or%20paed=Paed&research%20or%20clinic=Clinic&consult%20or%20sleep=Consult&first%20name=[FIRST_NAME]&last%20name=[LAST_NAME]&dob=[DOB]">click here</a> and complete your registration form before attending for your appointment.</p>
<p><strong>Referral</strong></p>
<p>Please email your referral to <a href="mailto:reception@woolcock.org.au">reception@woolcock.org.au</a> prior to your appointment.</p>
<p>Please note that an indefinite referral will only be accepted for a 12 month period before a new referral is required. A specialist referral is valid for 3 months and a GP referral is valid for 12 months.</p>
<p>Without a valid referral at the time of your consultation/treatment, Medicare will not be able to process your claim.</p>
<p>Approval documentation from your Insurer needs to be provided in the case of a Workers&rsquo; Compensation or Third-Party Claim. If not supplied, payment will need to be made on the day by the patient.</p>
<p>You will receive a confirmation SMS 96 hours before your appointment. To secure your appointment, you must SMS &lsquo;Yes&rdquo; to confirm your attendance.</p>
<p><strong>What to bring</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Your Medicare/DVA card/Pension card</li>
<li>Any test results (for example, blood tests, X-rays, scans)</li>
<li>A medication list or medications</li>
<li>During the COVID pandemic please ensure that you wear a mask at the clinic. This will help to ensure the safety and wellbeing of yourself and everyone you come in contact with at the clinic.</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Screening for COVID 19</strong></p>
<p>Please&nbsp;<strong>do not attend&nbsp;</strong>your appointment if:</p>
<ul>
<li>You have been diagnosed with COVID-19</li>
<li>You have had any of the following&nbsp;<a href="https://www.health.nsw.gov.au/Infectious/covid-19/Pages/frequently-asked-questions.aspx#1-4">symptomsâ€‹</a>&nbsp;in the last 14 days:&nbsp;&nbsp;</li>
<ul>
<li>fever (37.5&deg; or higher)</li>
<li>cough</li>
<li>sore throat</li>
<li>shortness of breath (difficulty breathing)</li>
<li>runny nose</li>
<li>loss of taste</li>
<li>loss of smell.</li>
</ul>
<li>You have developed any other respiratory symptoms</li>
<li>You have been a contact of someone diagnosed with COVID-19<strong>&nbsp;</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Payment for your consultation:</strong></p>
<p>The cost of your initial consultation will be between $280.00-$300.00, depending on the complexity of the consultation. If other services are required on the day, additional fees are payable. We accept EFTPOS, credit cards including AMEX without surcharge (no Diners Club), or cash. We may not able to submit your claim to Medicare on site.</p>
<p>As a private clinic appointments won&rsquo;t be Bulk Billed as a rule.</p>
<p>If you have any queries or require additional information, please do not hesitate in contacting us on 02 9805 3000.</p>
<p><strong>Cancellation Fees</strong></p>
<p>When a patient cancels their appointment or does not attend without giving notice, they prevent another patient from being seen.&nbsp; Therefore, your doctor requires a 48-hour cancellation notice for any appointment changes.</p>
<p>A charge of $100 will apply for any appointment changes that may occur without appropriate notice.&nbsp;</p>
<p>We look forward to welcoming you at the Woolcock Clinic and wish you all the best for your visit.</p>
